Task:
Create a cron job:
$ ssh tony@stapp01 
$ sudo su 
$ yum install cronie -y
$ systemctl start crond.service
$ systemctl status crond.service
$ crontab -e
$ crontab -l
$ ll /tmp/
Repeat same for the rest two application servers

Task: Linux User Files
$ ssh steve@stapp02
provide password
$ sudo su
password
$ ll /home/usersdata
$ ll /media
$ find /home/usersdata/ -type f -user kirsty |wc -l
$ find /home/usersdata/ -type f -user kirsty -exec cp --parent {} /media \; 
Ref: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2961673/find-missing-argument-to-exec
$ ll /media/home/usersdata/

Task: Linux User Without Home
$ ssh steve@stapp02
provide password then login as root user 
$ sudo su
$ id rose
$ cat /etc/passwd/ |grep rose
$ useradd -M rose
$ id rose
$ cat /etc/passwd/ |grep rose
$ ll /home/ 

Task: substitution of string in a file
$ ssh clint@stbkp01 then provide password as usual
$ sudo su login as root user
$ cat /root/nautilus.xml
$ sed -i 's/String/Topedo/g' /root/nautilus.xml

